&lt;p&gt;VIP is seeking a highly skilled &lt;strong&gt;IT Systems Engineer 3&lt;/strong&gt; to join our IT Systems Team. This role is pivotal in analyzing, testing, and building leading-edge solutions, focusing heavily on advanced process automation, security, and scalability. As an IT Systems Engineer 3, you will be a key leader in designing and implementing complex software systems, ensuring they are reliable, secure, and scalable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Full Time, Hybrid. This position will report to our office headquarters in Colchester, VT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automation &amp;amp; Scripting:&lt;/strong&gt; Achieve significant process automation using tools like &lt;strong&gt;Ansible&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;PowerShell&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;bash&lt;/strong&gt; to increase system efficiency and reduce manual intervention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Design &amp;amp; Implementation:&lt;/strong&gt; Design, implement, and maintain complex systems across our x64/x86 servers, applications, and virtualized environments. Implement web hosting technologies such as reverse proxies (HAProxy) and web servers (Tomcat, IIS).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced Troubleshooting:&lt;/strong&gt; Perform diagnosis of root cause for incidents, troubleshoot unique challenges, and execute full resolution steps, especially for VIP infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security &amp;amp; Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt; Implement and maintain robust system security measures, adhere to &lt;strong&gt;SOC1&amp;amp;2&lt;/strong&gt; security policies, and assist with audits. Work with 3rd-party cloud solutions (&lt;strong&gt;Akamai, Crowdstrike, Okta, Google, Microsoft&lt;/strong&gt;) where appropriate. Implement Identity and Access Management best practices where appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Mentoring:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with IT Security, Middleware, IBMi, and other teams. Provide technical guidance and mentorship to less experienced Systems Engineers (Level I, II).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategy &amp;amp; Research:&lt;/strong&gt; Research new tools and services, leading deployment projects from beta testing to full rollout, and staying current with emerging technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of progressive experience in software or systems engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field (relevant certifications and work experience may substitute for a degree).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid scripting and automation experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced understanding of &lt;strong&gt;Windows&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Linux&lt;/strong&gt; Servers, and networking knowledge (&lt;strong&gt;OSI layers, TCP/IP&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with &lt;strong&gt;cloud infrastructure&lt;/strong&gt; (AWS, Azure, GCP) and &lt;strong&gt;virtualization&lt;/strong&gt;/&lt;strong&gt;containerization&lt;/strong&gt; (Nutanix AHV/AOS is a plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with DevOps principles, Agile/Waterfall methodologies, and strong adherence to change control and documentation standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Industry certifications such as &lt;strong&gt;CCNA, MCSE, or CISSP&lt;/strong&gt; are a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analysis, critical thinking, and communication skills, with a methodical and detail-oriented approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
