&lt;p&gt;Looking for a fast-paced atmosphere where you can make your mark? The &lt;strong&gt;Senior Marketing Events Manager&lt;/strong&gt; owns VIP&#39;s event strategy as a pipeline engine and will be the first dedicated event manager &lt;em&gt;ever &lt;/em&gt;at our 50 year old org! You will design and execute a calendar of owned events, roadshows, and industry conference presences that generate qualified leads, accelerate deals, and deepen customer relationships. Events at VIP are not brand awareness plays — they are revenue vehicles. Success in this role will mean bringing your SaaS company event expertise and processes to a team that’s eager for your organization and project management. VIP has just undergone a rebrand. In this role, you will be helping to transform the outward face of VIP, its booth and event presence. You will own our customer summit where we invite over 500 customers to convene annually in a US city to learn about and expand their usage of our products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Full Time, Remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end strategy, planning, and execution for VIP&#39;s annual Summit, roadshows, and large and small beverage industry events&lt;/li&gt;
